│ The crash is an assertion failure in `llvm::slpvectorizer::BoUpSLP::isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry`:                                                                                │
│ `TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1 && "Expected only single user of a gather node."`                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This assertion is hit when running `opt -slp-vectorizer` on the provided LLVM IR. The backtrace indicates the crash happens during cost analysis of a potential vectorization candidate, │
│ specifically when checking for a gather pattern (`isGatherShuffledEntry`).                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The IR shows a `load` instruction (`%2`) that is used by two `icmp` instructions (`%cmp4.2` and `%cmp4.1`). The SLP vectorizer likely tries to vectorize these two `icmp` instructions.  │
│ In this scenario, the `load` (`%2`) is a common scalar operand to both instructions. In the SLP vectorizer's internal tree representation, the `TreeEntry` for this `load` will have two │
│ users (the `TreeEntry`s for the two `icmp`s).                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The function `isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry` is designed to handle a specific case of a gather where a single value is broadcast. The assertion `TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() ==  │
│ 1` enforces that the value being gathered has only one user in the vectorization tree. This assumption is too strict. A scalar value that is broadcast to form a vector can certainly be │
│ used by multiple operations within the vectorized group.                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ **2. Propose a fix**                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to remove the overly restrictive assertion. The logic within `isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry` already correctly handles the case of a single scalar value being          │
│ broadcast, regardless of how many users it has within the SLP tree. The number of users does not affect the validity of identifying it as a broadcast pattern. The existing code         │
│ correctly checks that all lanes of the gather refer to the same scalar value.                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Therefore, I will remove the assertion `assert(TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1 && "Expected only single user of a gather node.");` from                                               │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`.                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
